title: Art treasures of the Louvre (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
H.N. Abrams / 1951 / 178 pages / Pdf / English / 13.8 MB

As you open this book you virtually step inside the Louvre," says Rene de Messieres, Cultural Counselor to the French Embassy. Here is the heart of the fabulous collections of the Louvre, in the 100 paintings which are newly reproduced in full color with the greatest fidelity that modern science and artistry can achieve.

Supplementing this breathtaking array is a large number of monochromes of objects of art- sculpture, ceramics, enamels, and so on giving the illustrations altogether a range of about 4,000 years
